        <a title="Mogsy (MMOGC)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mogsy (MMOGC)" href="/user/show/4379514-mogsy-mmogc">Mogsy (MMOGC)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4379514-mogsy-mmogc?shelf=audiobook">audiobook</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4379514-mogsy-mmogc?shelf=horror">horror</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4379514-mogsy-mmogc?shelf=thriller-suspense">thriller-suspense</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4379514-mogsy-mmogc?shelf=zombies">zombies</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer330134055" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2322421775117150318">I didn&apos;t really enjoy this, even though it was well-written and had a good story. The thing is, it just wasn&apos;t my kind of story. Admittedly, I was misled by the cover and the description of this book to believe that it was mainly about zombies. It really isn&apos;t. I mean, they do play a role, but this turned out to be more of a thriller/suspense novel dealing with terrorism and covert ops, with the zombie threat only playing second fiddle. <br/><br/>I personally found it boring, but like I said, it&apos;s probabl</span>
  <span id="freeText2322421775117150318" style="display:none">I didn't really enjoy this, even though it was well-written and had a good story. The thing is, it just wasn't my kind of story. Admittedly, I was misled by the cover and the description of this book to believe that it was mainly about zombies. It really isn't. I mean, they do play a role, but this turned out to be more of a thriller/suspense novel dealing with terrorism and covert ops, with the zombie threat only playing second fiddle. <br /><br />I personally found it boring, but like I said, it's probably because this wasn't the book I expected. But you might like it if the war on terror meets the zombie plague is your thing.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2322421775117150318" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

